    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if its a worn sensor or if i messed up the caliper or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal when braking on a Camry, right after a brake pad replacement, is usually a sign that something is catching or rubbing. You should first check the caliper and the pads themselves, as a poorly seated pad or a sticking caliper is a common culprit. If you don't find anything obvious, you might need to look at the brake rotor for any warping, which can also cause squealing.",
