    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the pads and they look fine, but i can't really tell if the caliper is sticking or not. also the sound is super intermittent, sometimes it's loud and sometimes i don't hear it at all. is there a way to test if the caliper is actually stuck or is it just something else making that annoying noise?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since the noise is intermittent, it's a tricky one, and you need to get a good look at that caliper. A good test, if you're comfortable, is to try and manually move the caliper piston. See if it moves freely or if it feels gritty or stuck. If it feels stiff, that's your problem, and you might need to clean out any old grease or debris. Sometimes, a little bit of fresh, clean lubricant can smooth things out, though you'd want to be careful not to get any of that greasy muck on the rotor.",
      "source": "target",
