    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the piston moves okay i think, but the sound is driving me crazy. it just sounds so... random. like some weird, tiny screeching coming from somewhere inside the wheel well. almost sounds like something is living in there making noises for no reason. could it be a loose clip or something just vibrating weirdly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loose clip or vibration sounds like a very good place to start looking, especially when the noise is random. You should check all the hardware around the caliper assembly—the retaining clips, the bolts holding the caliper to the bracket, and even the dust boots. Sometimes a tiny piece of metal or a piece of grit gets wedged between two parts, and when you hit the brakes, it vibrates just enough to make that high-pitched screech.",
      "source": "target",
